issueDTO.description:
Currently shorthand `x=` syntax is only available for a small subset of operators:

```
add_op_eq        = @{ "+=" | "-=" | "*=" | "/=" | "%=" }
```

it would be nie to have this support for more operators, e.g. `x >>= 5`, `x ^= 6`, ...

This is relatively simple to do:
- add more operators to the Pest grammar;
- track `AddEqSymbol` in the parser library and add corresponding cases to it;
- in the compiler, implement the actual transformation `blah op= bloh` => `blah = blah op bloh` and codegen the latter (plenty of examples in `compiler-lib/src/do_compile/nodes/write_opeq_statement.rs`)
- this is a no-op from the VM's point of view

