@snehankekre could we just make SVGs take over the whole width of the container when no `width` is specified?

Today the default value for `use_column_width` is `"auto"` (although the docs say it's `None` for some reason...), which means "set the image's width to its natural size, but do not exceed the width of the column".

So we could change the meaning of `"auto"` to include "If the image is an SVG and no `width` is set, "auto" will make the image use the container width".

